

     
       Just Hum!  That's exactly what Fraunhofer Institut of Germany (the creators of the ubiquitous MP3 digital audio format) would have us do.  It's called " Query by Humming ," a type of melody recognition software program on display at this week's Midem music conference in Cannes that identifies a song by title and composer based on a person humming a few bars into a microphone.  Sounds like a cool thing, doesn't it?! Read more  urlLink here .  [via  urlLink Metafilter ]  
     
    
